						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Kaḷappāḻkuḍi a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Miṟaikkūṟṟam for the daily supply of an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruchchōṟṟuttuṟai-Mādēva by••••<hi rend="bold">Nambaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kaṇṭakachaṇḍavāraṇa-Pēraraiyaṉ of Kayalūr</hi> in Maṇṇi-nāḍu. To judge by his title, the donor should have been a military chief of some note.</p>						

						</summary>
